{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TQSMzjeca6mFtFLP4K1pR6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017nyuCSSxCM7nDMCKebGC39","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/findings.txt","content":"RabbitMQ Compliance Audit Report\n=================================\nNamespace : karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-5f809e96-cluster-a\nAudit date: 2026-06-25\nAuditor   : read-only automated inspection (no changes made)\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n1. CLUSTER HEALTH\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nNodes (3/3 running, no maintenance, no alarms, no network partitions):\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-0  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-1  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-2  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n\nUptime (rabbitmq-0): ~1266 s at audit time\nAlarms           : none\nNetwork partitions: none\nUnder maintenance: none\n\nMemory (rabbitmq-0):\n  Used      : 0.1677 GB\n  High-water: 40% of available (~5.43 GB)\n  Free disk : 883.8 GB (low-watermark 0.05 GB вЂ” well clear)\n\nConnections: 0 active at audit time\nQueues     : 2 (cluster-wide)\nVhosts     : 3\n\n[FINDING C1 вЂ” OUT-OF-SUPPORT VERSION]\n  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 is listed as \"out of support\" (rabbitmqctl status\n  output). The current supported series at audit time is 3.13.x / 4.x.\n  Recommend scheduling an upgrade.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n2. VIRTUAL HOSTS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  /       (default вЂ” no non-admin permissions, no queues, no policies)\n  /app    (application workload vhost)\n  /ops    (operations/monitoring vhost)\n\nNo vhost-level resource limits are set on any vhost.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n3. USERS & PERMISSIONS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  User      Tags            Vhost access\n  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ    в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ    в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n  admin     administrator   /  в†’ configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n                            /app в†’ configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n                            /ops в†’ configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n  app-user  management      /app в†’ configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n  ops-user  management      /ops в†’ configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n\nGuest account (built-in \"guest\"):\n  The guest user is NOT present in the user list (removed or never\n  enabled with this name). The config sets loopback_users.guest = false\n  (allowing guest access from non-loopback addresses), but since the\n  user does not exist, this is effectively a non-issue. Recommend\n  setting loopback_users.guest = true (or leaving the default) to\n  prevent accidental re-creation with open access.\n\n[FINDING U1 вЂ” BROAD WILDCARD PERMISSIONS]\n  Both app-user and ops-user have configure=.* write=.* read=.*\n  on their respective vhosts. This grants full resource creation/deletion\n  rights, not just message pub/sub. Least-privilege would restrict\n  configure to \"\" (empty) for application service accounts.\n\n[FINDING U2 вЂ” MANAGEMENT TAG ON SERVICE ACCOUNTS]\n  app-user and ops-user carry the \"management\" tag, giving them access\n  to the HTTP management API (stats, node info). If these accounts are\n  used by automated services, management API access is unnecessary and\n  increases the attack surface.\n\n[FINDING U3 вЂ” ADMIN WITH FULL ACCESS TO ALL VHOSTS]\n  The admin user has unrestricted permissions on /, /app, and /ops.\n  If admin credentials are compromised, all vhosts are exposed. Consider\n  a break-glass admin per-vhost pattern or vhost-scoped admin accounts.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n4. POLICIES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  Vhost /app:\n    Name   : ha-all\n    Pattern: .*  (applies to all queues)\n    Apply-to: queues\n    Definition: {\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}\n    Priority: 0\n\n  Vhost /ops: (none)\n  Vhost /   : (none)\n\n[FINDING P1 вЂ” CLASSIC MIRRORED QUEUES (DEPRECATED)]\n  The ha-all policy uses ha-mode:all with classic mirrored queue\n  semantics. Classic mirrored queues are deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.12\n  and removed in 4.x. The recommended replacement is Quorum Queues,\n  which offer stronger consistency and durability. The current queues\n  in /app are declared as \"classic\" type.\n\n[FINDING P2 вЂ” ha-mode:all MIRRORS TO EVERY NODE]\n  ha-mode:all means every message is mirrored to all 3 nodes. For a\n  3-node cluster this provides maximum redundancy but at the cost of\n  3Г— write amplification. Consider ha-mode:exactly with count=2 if\n  write throughput becomes a concern.\n\n[FINDING P3 вЂ” NO POLICY ON /ops VHOST]\n  The ops-queue in /ops has no HA policy. If this queue holds\n  operational data that must survive a node failure, a policy should\n  be applied (or ops-queue should be converted to a quorum queue).\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n5. QUEUES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  Vhost /app:\n    app-queue  type=classic  durable=true  args=[x-queue-type:classic]\n\n  Vhost /ops:\n    ops-queue  type=classic  durable=true  args=[x-queue-type:classic]\n\n  (No queues in vhost /.)\n\nBoth queues are durable (survive broker restarts). No dead-letter\nexchanges, TTLs, max-length, or other arguments are configured.\n\n[FINDING Q1 вЂ” CLASSIC QUEUE TYPE]\n  Both queues are declared with x-queue-type=classic. As noted in P1,\n  this type is deprecated. Migration to quorum queues is recommended\n  before upgrading to RabbitMQ 4.x.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n6. TLS / TRANSPORT SECURITY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nListeners (all nodes, per rabbitmqctl cluster_status):\n  Port 5672  вЂ” AMQP (plain TCP, no TLS)\n  Port 15672 вЂ” HTTP management (plain HTTP, no TLS)\n  Port 15692 вЂ” Prometheus metrics (plain HTTP)\n  Port 25672 вЂ” inter-node clustering / CLI (no TLS)\n\nSSL configuration from environment:\n  ssl_listeners  : []   (TLS AMQP listener NOT enabled)\n  ssl_options    : []   (no cert/key configured)\n  Accepted TLS versions (if TLS were enabled): tlsv1.3, tlsv1.2\n\n[FINDING T1 вЂ” NO TLS ON AMQP LISTENER]\n  Client connections use plain AMQP on port 5672. Credentials and\n  messages are transmitted in cleartext over the network. TLS should\n  be enabled on the AMQP listener for any environment carrying\n  sensitive data.\n\n[FINDING T2 вЂ” MANAGEMENT API UNENCRYPTED]\n  The management API (port 15672) and Prometheus endpoint (15692) are\n  served over plain HTTP. Admin credentials sent to the management API\n  are exposed in transit.\n\n[FINDING T3 вЂ” INTER-NODE TRAFFIC UNENCRYPTED]\n  Inter-node clustering on port 25672 is not TLS-wrapped. On a flat\n  Kubernetes pod network this traffic is visible to any pod with\n  network access to the headless service.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n7. AUTHENTICATION & SECURITY SETTINGS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  auth_backends          : rabbit_auth_backend_internal (internal only)\n  auth_mechanisms        : PLAIN, AMQPLAIN\n  password_hashing_module: rabbit_password_hashing_sha256\n  track_auth_attempt_source: false\n  loopback_users.guest   : false (configured in both rabbitmq.conf and\n                           10-defaults.conf; redundant but not harmful)\n\n[FINDING A1 вЂ” PLAIN / AMQPLAIN MECHANISMS WITHOUT TLS]\n  PLAIN and AMQPLAIN transmit credentials in base64-encoded (effectively\n  cleartext) form. Without TLS on the AMQP listener (see T1), passwords\n  are recoverable from network traffic.\n\n[FINDING A2 вЂ” AUTH ATTEMPT SOURCE TRACKING DISABLED]\n  track_auth_attempt_source = false means failed authentication attempts\n  are not recorded with source IP. This limits forensic capability and\n  brute-force detection.\n\n[FINDING A3 вЂ” NO EXTERNAL AUTH BACKEND]\n  Authentication relies solely on the internal RabbitMQ database. No\n  LDAP, OAuth2, or mTLS certificate-based auth is configured. For\n  compliance environments, an external IdP integration is often required.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n8. PLUGINS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nEnabled plugins:\n  rabbitmq_management          вЂ” HTTP management API (enabled)\n  rabbitmq_management_agent    вЂ” per-node stats collection\n  rabbitmq_prometheus          вЂ” Prometheus metrics endpoint\n  rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s  вЂ” Kubernetes peer discovery\n  rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common\n  prometheus, accept, amqp_client, cowboy, cowlib, rabbitmq_web_dispatch\n\n[FINDING PL1 вЂ” MANAGEMENT PLUGIN ENABLED IN PRODUCTION]\n  The management plugin adds an unauthenticated-to-start HTTP surface\n  (port 15672). If external access to this port is not restricted by\n  NetworkPolicy or firewall, it increases the attack surface. Verify\n  that a Kubernetes NetworkPolicy limits access to this port.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n9. KUBERNETES RESOURCE SUMMARY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nPods:\n  rabbitmq-0          Running  (broker)\n  rabbitmq-1          Running  (broker)\n  rabbitmq-2          Running  (broker)\n  rabbitmq-setup-*    Completed (setup job, done)\n  app-producer-*      Running  (workload)\n  app-client-*        Running  (workload)\n  ops-client-*        Running  (workload)\n  curl-test           Running  (test pod)\n  prometheus-*        Running  (metrics scraper)\n\nSecrets (names only вЂ” contents not inspected):\n  rabbitmq-admin         (admin credentials)\n  rabbitmq-app           (app-user credentials)\n  rabbitmq-ops           (ops-user credentials)\n  rabbitmq-erlang-cookie (inter-node auth cookie)\n\nCluster partition-handling policy: pause_minority\n  (safe default: minority partition pauses rather than split-braining)\n\nQueue master locator: min-masters\n  (distributes queue masters across nodes)\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n10. FINDING SUMMARY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nSeverity legend: HIGH = immediate remediation recommended\n                 MEDIUM = remediation before next change window\n                 LOW = improvement / best practice\n\n  ID   Severity  Category        Summary\n  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n  C1   MEDIUM    Version         RabbitMQ 3.12.14 is out of support\n  U1   MEDIUM    Permissions     Service accounts have configure=.* (too broad)\n  U2   LOW       Permissions     Service accounts carry management tag\n  U3   MEDIUM    Permissions     admin has full access to all vhosts\n  P1   HIGH      Deprecation     ha-all policy uses deprecated classic mirroring\n  P2   LOW       Tuning          ha-mode:all causes 3Г— write amplification\n  P3   MEDIUM    Availability    /ops vhost has no HA policy on ops-queue\n  Q1   HIGH      Deprecation     Both queues are classic type (removed in 4.x)\n  T1   HIGH      Transport       No TLS on AMQP listener (credentials cleartext)\n  T2   HIGH      Transport       Management API over plain HTTP\n  T3   MEDIUM    Transport       Inter-node traffic not TLS-wrapped\n  A1   HIGH      Auth            PLAIN/AMQPLAIN without TLS = exposed passwords\n  A2   LOW       Auth            Auth attempt source tracking disabled\n  A3   LOW       Auth            No external auth backend (internal DB only)\n  PL1  LOW       Attack surface  Management plugin enabled; verify NetworkPolicy\n\nTotal: 5 HIGH, 5 MEDIUM, 5 LOW\nNo changes were made to the cluster during this audit.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":673,"cache_read_input_tokens":39003,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":673},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3096-e4c2-4f4d-89a0-82e6fdf3682a","uuid":"84da2dad-a3b1-4256-b85a-f649d5f0a390","request_id":"req_011CcQ65yn6afqQnbUgPZgpA"}
