{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EcQ7323FAqbivAXg7jqSwY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013KFyu6Spzjq5u261kQmZ7x","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/findings.txt << 'FINDINGS_EOF'\nRabbitMQ Compliance Audit Report\n=================================\nNamespace : karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-5f809e96-cluster-a\nAudit date: 2026-06-25\nAuditor   : read-only automated inspection (no changes made)\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n1. CLUSTER HEALTH\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nNodes (3/3 running, no maintenance, no alarms, no network partitions):\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-0  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-1  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n  rabbit@rabbitmq-2  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15  disk  RUNNING\n\nUptime (rabbitmq-0): ~1266 s at audit time\nAlarms            : none\nNetwork partitions: none\nUnder maintenance : none\n\nMemory (rabbitmq-0):\n  Used      : 0.1677 GB\n  High-water: 40% of available (~5.43 GB)\n  Free disk : 883.8 GB  (low-watermark 0.05 GB вЂ” well clear)\n\nActive connections: 0\nTotal queues      : 2 (cluster-wide)\nVirtual hosts     : 3\n\n[FINDING C1 вЂ” OUT-OF-SUPPORT VERSION]\n  RabbitMQ 3.12.14 is listed as \"out of support\" in rabbitmqctl status.\n  The supported series at audit time is 3.13.x / 4.x.\n  Recommend scheduling an upgrade.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n2. VIRTUAL HOSTS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  /       (default вЂ” admin-only permissions, no queues, no policies)\n  /app    (application workload vhost)\n  /ops    (operations/monitoring vhost)\n\nNo vhost-level resource limits are configured on any vhost.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n3. USERS & PERMISSIONS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  User      Tags            Vhost  configure  write  read\n  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n  admin     administrator   /      .*         .*     .*\n                            /app   .*         .*     .*\n                            /ops   .*         .*     .*\n  app-user  management      /app   .*         .*     .*\n  ops-user  management      /ops   .*         .*     .*\n\nGuest account: The built-in \"guest\" user does not exist in this cluster.\n  Note: loopback_users.guest = false is set in both config files, which\n  would allow guest to connect from non-loopback addresses if that user\n  were re-created. Recommend reverting to the default (= true) as a\n  defence-in-depth measure.\n\n[FINDING U1 вЂ” BROAD WILDCARD PERMISSIONS]\n  app-user and ops-user hold configure=.* on their vhosts, granting full\n  resource creation and deletion rights, not just publish/subscribe.\n  Least-privilege would restrict configure to \"\" (empty) for service\n  accounts.\n\n[FINDING U2 вЂ” MANAGEMENT TAG ON SERVICE ACCOUNTS]\n  app-user and ops-user carry the \"management\" tag, granting access to\n  the HTTP management API (stats, node info, queue browser). Automated\n  service accounts do not require this; it unnecessarily increases the\n  attack surface.\n\n[FINDING U3 вЂ” ADMIN ACCESS SPANS ALL VHOSTS]\n  The admin user has unrestricted permissions on /, /app, and /ops.\n  A single compromised credential exposes all vhosts. Consider vhost-\n  scoped admin accounts or a break-glass pattern.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n4. POLICIES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  Vhost /app:\n    Name      : ha-all\n    Pattern   : .*  (matches all queues)\n    Apply-to  : queues\n    Definition: {\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"}\n    Priority  : 0\n\n  Vhost /ops: (no policies)\n  Vhost /   : (no policies)\n\n[FINDING P1 вЂ” CLASSIC MIRRORED QUEUES (DEPRECATED)]\n  The ha-all policy applies classic mirrored-queue semantics\n  (ha-mode:all). Classic mirrored queues are deprecated in RabbitMQ\n  3.12 and removed in 4.x. The recommended replacement is Quorum\n  Queues, which provide stronger guarantees via Raft consensus.\n\n[FINDING P2 вЂ” ha-mode:all ON A 3-NODE CLUSTER]\n  Mirroring to all 3 nodes maximises redundancy but also means 3Г—\n  write amplification for every published message. If write throughput\n  becomes a concern, ha-mode:exactly with count=2 achieves N-1 fault\n  tolerance at lower cost.\n\n[FINDING P3 вЂ” NO HA POLICY ON /ops VHOST]\n  ops-queue in /ops is a classic durable queue with no HA policy\n  attached. If this queue must survive a node failure, a policy should\n  be applied (or ops-queue should be converted to a quorum queue).\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n5. QUEUES\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  Vhost  Queue      Type     Durable  Arguments\n  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n  /app   app-queue  classic  true     x-queue-type=classic\n  /ops   ops-queue  classic  true     x-queue-type=classic\n\nNo DLX, TTL, max-length, or overflow arguments are set on either queue.\nNo queues exist in the default (/) vhost.\n\n[FINDING Q1 вЂ” CLASSIC QUEUE TYPE]\n  Both queues are declared with x-queue-type=classic. This type is\n  deprecated and will not be supported in RabbitMQ 4.x. Migration to\n  quorum queues is recommended before any version upgrade.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n6. TLS / TRANSPORT SECURITY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nActive listeners (all three nodes):\n  Port 5672  вЂ” AMQP      (plain TCP вЂ” NO TLS)\n  Port 15672 вЂ” HTTP mgmt (plain HTTP вЂ” NO TLS)\n  Port 15692 вЂ” Prometheus (plain HTTP вЂ” NO TLS)\n  Port 25672 вЂ” inter-node clustering / CLI (plain TCP вЂ” NO TLS)\n\nSSL configuration (from rabbitmqctl environment):\n  ssl_listeners : []  (TLS AMQP listener NOT enabled)\n  ssl_options   : []  (no certificate/key path configured)\n  Supported TLS versions (if TLS were enabled): TLSv1.3, TLSv1.2\n\n[FINDING T1 вЂ” NO TLS ON AMQP LISTENER]\n  Client connections use plain AMQP on port 5672. Credentials and\n  message payloads are transmitted in cleartext. TLS must be enabled\n  for any environment handling sensitive data.\n\n[FINDING T2 вЂ” MANAGEMENT API AND PROMETHEUS OVER PLAIN HTTP]\n  Admin credentials sent to port 15672 and metrics on port 15692 are\n  exposed in transit. TLS should be applied to these listeners.\n\n[FINDING T3 вЂ” INTER-NODE TRAFFIC NOT ENCRYPTED]\n  Clustering traffic on port 25672 is not TLS-wrapped. On a shared\n  Kubernetes pod network, this traffic is visible to any pod that can\n  reach the rabbitmq-headless service.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n7. AUTHENTICATION & SECURITY SETTINGS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  auth_backends            : rabbit_auth_backend_internal (only)\n  auth_mechanisms          : PLAIN, AMQPLAIN\n  password_hashing_module  : rabbit_password_hashing_sha256\n  track_auth_attempt_source: false\n  loopback_users.guest     : false (set in both config files)\n\n[FINDING A1 вЂ” PLAIN/AMQPLAIN WITHOUT TLS]\n  PLAIN and AMQPLAIN encode credentials as base64 (effectively\n  cleartext). Without TLS on the AMQP listener (T1), passwords are\n  trivially recoverable from network captures.\n\n[FINDING A2 вЂ” AUTH ATTEMPT SOURCE TRACKING DISABLED]\n  track_auth_attempt_source = false means failed authentication events\n  are not logged with source IP, limiting brute-force detection and\n  forensic capability.\n\n[FINDING A3 вЂ” INTERNAL AUTH ONLY]\n  No LDAP, OAuth2, or mTLS certificate-based backend is configured.\n  For compliance environments requiring centralised identity management,\n  an external IdP integration should be evaluated.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n8. ENABLED PLUGINS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\n  rabbitmq_management          (HTTP management API вЂ” port 15672)\n  rabbitmq_management_agent    (per-node stats collection)\n  rabbitmq_prometheus          (Prometheus metrics вЂ” port 15692)\n  rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s  (Kubernetes peer discovery)\n  rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common\n  prometheus, accept, amqp_client, cowboy, cowlib, rabbitmq_web_dispatch\n\n[FINDING PL1 вЂ” MANAGEMENT PLUGIN SCOPE]\n  The management plugin exposes an additional HTTP API surface\n  (port 15672). Verify that a Kubernetes NetworkPolicy restricts\n  access to this port to authorised clients only.\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n9. KUBERNETES RESOURCES (READ-ONLY OBSERVATION)\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nPods at audit time:\n  rabbitmq-0           Running    (broker node 0)\n  rabbitmq-1           Running    (broker node 1)\n  rabbitmq-2           Running    (broker node 2)\n  rabbitmq-setup-*     Completed  (one-time setup job)\n  app-producer-*       Running    (message producer workload)\n  app-client-*         Running    (application consumer)\n  ops-client-*         Running    (operations consumer)\n  curl-test            Running    (test/debug pod)\n  prometheus-*         Running    (metrics scraper)\n\nSecrets (names only вЂ” contents not read):\n  rabbitmq-admin         (admin credentials)\n  rabbitmq-app           (app-user credentials)\n  rabbitmq-ops           (ops-user credentials)\n  rabbitmq-erlang-cookie (inter-node Erlang cookie)\n\nCluster settings:\n  Partition handling: pause_minority (safe default)\n  Queue master locator: min-masters (distributes primaries across nodes)\n  Global cluster ID: rabbitmq-cluster-id-MKGrDm77zPjzAHwRZdJWLQ\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n10. FEATURE FLAGS\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nAll nodes report the same feature flag state (consistent cluster):\n  classic_mirrored_queue_version  ENABLED\n  classic_queue_type_delivery_support ENABLED\n  quorum_queue                    ENABLED\n  stream_queue                    ENABLED\n  feature_flags_v2                ENABLED\n  (and 10 others вЂ” all enabled on all nodes)\n\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n11. FINDING SUMMARY\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\n\nSeverity: HIGH = immediate remediation recommended\n          MEDIUM = remediate before next change window\n          LOW = improvement / best practice\n\n  ID   Sev     Category       Summary\n  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\n  C1   MEDIUM  Version        RabbitMQ 3.12.14 out of support\n  U1   MEDIUM  Permissions    Service accounts have configure=.* (too broad)\n  U2   LOW     Permissions    Service accounts carry unnecessary management tag\n  U3   MEDIUM  Permissions    admin has unrestricted access to all vhosts\n  P1   HIGH    Deprecation    ha-all policy uses deprecated classic mirroring\n  P2   LOW     Tuning         ha-mode:all causes 3Г— write amplification\n  P3   MEDIUM  Availability   /ops vhost has no HA policy on ops-queue\n  Q1   HIGH    Deprecation    Both queues are classic type (removed in 4.x)\n  T1   HIGH    Transport      No TLS on AMQP listener вЂ” credentials cleartext\n  T2   HIGH    Transport      Management API and Prometheus over plain HTTP\n  T3   MEDIUM  Transport      Inter-node clustering traffic unencrypted\n  A1   HIGH    Auth           PLAIN/AMQPLAIN without TLS exposes passwords\n  A2   LOW     Auth           Auth attempt source tracking disabled\n  A3   LOW     Auth           No external auth backend configured\n  PL1  LOW     Attack surface Verify NetworkPolicy on management plugin port\n\nTotal: 5 HIGH В· 5 MEDIUM В· 5 LOW\n\nNo changes were made to the cluster configuration during this audit.\nFINDINGS_EOF\necho \"Written OK\"","description":"Write findings.txt to /tmp"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3523,"cache_read_input_tokens":39676,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3523},"output_tokens":47,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3096-e4c2-4f4d-89a0-82e6fdf3682a","uuid":"03a0cdf6-22cc-42cf-a2d4-881f1a9de253","request_id":"req_011CcQ6AgWAxRndoghg5RobY"}
