{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HiLJAJGuyGgcn5U26U49KB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `config-audit` ConfigMap has been created with a 14,678-byte `findings.txt`. Here's what the audit found (read-only вЂ” no changes made):\n\n**Cluster health:** All 3 nodes running, no alarms, no partitions.\n\n**15 findings across 5 HIGH / 5 MEDIUM / 5 LOW:**\n\n| Severity | Finding |\n|----------|---------|\n| HIGH | No TLS on AMQP (port 5672) вЂ” credentials in cleartext |\n| HIGH | Management API (15672) and Prometheus (15692) over plain HTTP |\n| HIGH | PLAIN/AMQPLAIN auth mechanisms without TLS |\n| HIGH | `ha-all` policy uses **deprecated** classic mirrored queues (removed in 4.x) |\n| HIGH | Both queues declared as `classic` type (also removed in 4.x) |\n| MEDIUM | RabbitMQ 3.12.14 is **out of support** |\n| MEDIUM | Service accounts (`app-user`, `ops-user`) have `configure=.*` вЂ” too broad |\n| MEDIUM | `admin` user has unrestricted access across all 3 vhosts |\n| MEDIUM | `/ops` vhost has no HA policy вЂ” `ops-queue` has no mirror/quorum protection |\n| MEDIUM | Inter-node clustering traffic (port 25672) unencrypted |\n| LOW | Service accounts carry `management` tag unnecessarily |\n| LOW | `ha-mode:all` causes 3Г— write amplification |\n| LOW | Auth attempt source tracking disabled |\n| LOW | No external auth backend (LDAP/OAuth2/mTLS) |\n| LOW | Verify NetworkPolicy restricts management API port |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":149,"cache_read_input_tokens":46904,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":149},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"350a3096-e4c2-4f4d-89a0-82e6fdf3682a","uuid":"b686c8db-aefc-48cb-a590-80b275f00dd0","request_id":"re